 663:../.././hal//stm32f3/stm32f3_hal_lowlevel.c ****   * @brief  Set or clear the selected data port bit.
 664:../.././hal//stm32f3/stm32f3_hal_lowlevel.c ****   *
 665:../.././hal//stm32f3/stm32f3_hal_lowlevel.c ****   * @note   This function uses GPIOx_BSRR and GPIOx_BRR registers to allow atomic read/modify
 666:../.././hal//stm32f3/stm32f3_hal_lowlevel.c ****   *         accesses. In this way, there is no risk of an IRQ occurring between
 667:../.././hal//stm32f3/stm32f3_hal_lowlevel.c ****   *         the read and the modify access.
 668:../.././hal//stm32f3/stm32f3_hal_lowlevel.c ****   *
 669:../.././hal//stm32f3/stm32f3_hal_lowlevel.c ****   * @param  GPIOx: where x can be (A..F) to select the GPIO peripheral for STM32F3 family
 670:../.././hal//stm32f3/stm32f3_hal_lowlevel.c ****   * @param  GPIO_Pin: specifies the port bit to be written.
 671:../.././hal//stm32f3/stm32f3_hal_lowlevel.c ****   *         This parameter can be one of GPIO_PIN_x where x can be (0..15).
 672:../.././hal//stm32f3/stm32f3_hal_lowlevel.c ****   * @param  PinState: specifies the value to be written to the selected bit.
 673:../.././hal//stm32f3/stm32f3_hal_lowlevel.c ****   *         This parameter can be one of the GPIO_PinState enum values:
 674:../.././hal//stm32f3/stm32f3_hal_lowlevel.c ****   *            @arg GPIO_PIN_RESET: to clear the port pin
 675:../.././hal//stm32f3/stm32f3_hal_lowlevel.c ****   *            @arg GPIO_PIN_SET: to set the port pin
 676:../.././hal//stm32f3/stm32f3_hal_lowlevel.c ****   * @retval None
 677:../.././hal//stm32f3/stm32f3_hal_lowlevel.c ****   */
 678:../.././hal//stm32f3/stm32f3_hal_lowlevel.c **** 
